{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> βρᾰδύς</b>, εῖα, ύ: <br /> <i>comparative</i> βραδύτερος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.8; _metathesis_ βαρδύτερος 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 29.30; βραδίων 2nd c.AD: Artemidorus Daldianus Onirocriticus 1.70 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>superlative</i> βραδύτατος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Fragmenta” 357, also βράδιστος (_metathesis_ βάρδιστος 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.310, 530, Doroth(?).cited in 7th c.AD: Hephaestio Grammaticus “Astr.” 3.30) 2nd c.AD: Aretaeus Medicus “περὶ αἰτιῶν καὶ σημείων χρονίων παθῶν” 1.6, βραδίστατος 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “Fragmenta” 325 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>slow</b>, κιχάνει τοι β. ὠκύν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.329, etc.: with \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>infinitive</i>, ἀλλά τοι ἵπποι βάρδιστοι θείειν <b>slowest</b> at running, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.310; β. λέγειν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 237, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ β. <b>delay</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 766e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. <i>adverb</i> βραδέως, χωρεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.70; θεῖν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 336a, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>comparative</i> <b>-ύτερον</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “προγνωστικόν” 22, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 190a; βραδυτέρως 4th c.BC: Aeneas Tacticus 16.12; βράδῐον 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 528, 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus 1.117 (condemned by 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Sol.” 7)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>superlative</i> <b>-ύτατα</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 39b. \">Refs 5th c.